    "The TCA (tricarboxylic acid) cycle metabolites (citric acid, aconitic acid, α-ketoglutarate, succinate, fumarate, malate, ATP, NAD) were decreased in LEGOs compared to the WT organoids (Fig. 4e and Supplementary Fig.",
    "4b, f), suggesting a shift toward glycolysis from oxidative phosphorylation, reminiscent of the Warburg effect.",
    "Metabolites are essential substrates of many epigenetic enzymes 31.",
    "We analyzed metabolite changes that may explain",
